Other than the terrible "Holding for Hux" joke at the start of the film
column83:
Star Wars: The Last Jedi is a cracking movie with more WTF moments than you would expect. And that\'s the point.
I can understand some people see this film and just think it\'s awful. I get it. It\'s nothing that any of us expected. It was a curve ball of the highest order.
I saw the first film in 1977 and that was it for me. Hooked. Complete fan boy for as long as I can remember. I care what happens to the characters.
Is it the Star Wars movie that I would have made. Nope. It\'s not. But what Rian Johnson has done is blasted the series wide open. Star Wars is no longer black and white. it\'s grey and unpredictable.
Luke Skywalker\'s path in the movie is just brilliant. I think one major point in the film is that Luke himself believes that (and he says as much) he cant just walk out and go at the First Order with his "lazer sword". As he pushes passed the regret he held in the movie he realises that in order to truly help
column84: he must become "more powerful than you can possibly imagine". How? At the time of the Force Awakens

column101:
and setting himself up for his own trilogy of films instead of focusing on the task at hand in making a great sequel to The Force Awakens.

Almost everything misses the mark in this film and it\'s place within the Star Wars lure/canon. Instead of writing out all of the problems with this film
column102:
I will list them as I\'m sure you\'ve seen this film and have an idea of what I\'m talking about.

-Time: We\'re led to believe that this film takes place over a course of 12 or so hours while the First Order engages the Resistance in a OJ Simpsonesque - low speed chase. However multiple days pass while Rey is on the island with Luke. This film is supposed to pick up right after TFA. How is this possible?
- The unnecessary inclusion of Laura Dern\'s character. Who is she? Where did she come from? Star Wars is now relying on it\'s audience to read supplemental material instead of adding exposition in the film. This character in every way could have been played by Admiral Ackbar
column103:
a legendary character who deserved more than a briefly mentioned off screen death.

You know this movie is no good. I don\'t need to keep going. I just hope Disney sees this and realizes they\'re actively ruining a classic franchise. '
